# Force LF in the working tree for all text files. Windows-side tooling kept CRLF-ing checkouts,
# which broke real things: guard-cs-read.sh's shebang became "bash\r" (every hook invocation then
# failed open), and CRLF inside test raw-string literals failed two CompactFormatter tests. Shell
# scripts, C# sources, and hook JSON are load-bearing about this; the blanket rule keeps diffs
# clean everywhere else too.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.cs text eol=lf
*.csproj text eol=lf
hooks/hooks.json text eol=lf
